The paper focuses on applying Deep Learning techniques to source code, specifically using a Neural Machine Translation (NMT) model to learn and replicate code changes implemented by developers during pull requests. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and natural language processing (cs.CL), as the NMT model is used to translate code changes into a different form. The paper also involves training and experimenting with the NMT model, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for novel research in the area of DL on code, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
